answers.q: ansoluta model e1205 how to connect
answers.a: E1205 is Basic methacrylate copolymer, a synthetic film-forming coating used on tablets/capsules in solid food supplements; it isn’t a device and doesn’t connect to anything.

answers.q: how to reset samsung gt e1205 network lock
answers.a: E1205 here refers to a food additive (basic methacrylate copolymer) used as a tablet/capsule coating, so there’s no network lock to reset.

answers.q: how to reset samsung gt e1205 network lock for free
answers.a: E1205 is a food additive, not a phone, so it has no network functions to reset; it’s used as a film-forming glaze on solid food supplements.

answers.q: how to take phone number off of the rejected call list on a samsung gt-e1205
answers.a: E1205 is an additive (basic methacrylate copolymer), not a handset; it’s used to coat tablets/capsules for taste-masking and protection.

answers.q: how to turn on the e1205
answers.a: As an E-number, E1205 is a polymer coating used in solid food supplements; it isn’t an electronic device you can turn on.
